  "source": "Theorem:\n. \"Theorem 4.37\"\ngiven:\n. X is \\set\nwhere:\n. forAll: A is \\set\n  where:\n  . A \"in\" X\n  then:\n  . not:\n    . A = \\empty.set\nthen:\n. exists: f is \\choice.function:on{X}\nDocumented:\n. description: \"Assuming the axioms of ZF and the well ordering principle, the axiom of choice holds. Well order $\\bigcup_{A \\in X} A$; then the function sending each $A \\in X$ to its least element is a choice function. This completes the equivalence of the axiom of choice, Zorn's lemma, and the well ordering principle.\"\nId: \"252a3455-3de4-4d4a-b258-b918cbd0c09d\"",
